Renders all subobject instances of a single category on a page.

Dispatches each instance through the auto-generated
`<category>/subobject-row` template, so each row uses the same
baked-params fast path as top-level dispatchers. One `#ask` query
regardless of subobject count.

Differs from Category/subobjects: this takes one explicit category
and skips the ancestor walk. Use when you want a specific subobject
type in a custom display (e.g. "show chapters here"). Use
Category/subobjects when you want all subobject types auto-discovered
from the category's inheritance chain.

 {{Category/subobject-list | category=Chapter | page={{FULLPAGENAME}} }}

Requires `<Category>/subobject-row` to exist — every category with at
least one Subobject field gets one generated automatically.

Parameters:
* category - Subobject category name (without namespace prefix).
* page     - Parent page whose subobjects should be listed.
             Defaults to {{FULLPAGENAME}}.
</noinclude>
